Class Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • Type
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayType, FunctionType

    public class Type
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementation of a generic type object. The type is represented by the type expression: T(t1, ...,tn). An attribute size was added for compiler needs.

        public boolean isCompatible(Type t)
        Tests if two types are compatible. For simple types, compatibility is equality of types. Sub-types (e.g. function types) must override this function accordingly.
